overview: The user wanted a thorough browser-based test of their sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent started by checking the dev server and
  navigating to the application's main page. After observing the questionnaire
  form and attempting to test validation by clicking "Next Section" without
  input, the agent realized there were validation blocks. To efficiently test
  the report generation, the agent examined the form's source code to understand
  its structure and then utilized a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button.
  This allowed the agent to quickly populate the form with mock data and proceed
  to the report section, setting the stage for further testing of the report
  functionality.
